cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for the classification of liver lesions in CT images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of pre-trained weights and fully connected layers for classification, which are common techniques in deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also has a medical application, which suggests cs.MED (Medical Imaging) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of image retrieval techniques, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a less likely but still possible category.
